      "side": 1,
      "message": "Isn\u0027t it redundant ith check on line 624?\nip6_ext_header_len_s() only reads from p when ip6_ext_hdr(nh) is true or nh \u003d\u003d IPSEC_AH; in both cases the minimum returned value is 8 ((0+1)\u003c\u003c3 and (0+2)\u003c\u003c2 respectively, with n_data_u64s being u8). So the existing check ip6_ext_header_len_s() + offset \u003e max_offset always fires first for any value of the length byte. For all other protocols the function returns a fixed constant or 0 without reading from p at all.",
      "revId": "24e1d24fe11d9351ddce2994bc142496250e61bd",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
