      "writtenOn": "2026-03-06T10:20:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I am not mistaken, in every callsite, sr0 is set via ip6_ext_header_find(), which calls ip6_ext_header_walk() and returns NULL if it returns -1. For ip6_ext_header_walk() to succeed and return a non-NULL sr0, it must have passed: sr_len + offset \u003c\u003d max_offset \u003c\u003d sizeof(ip6_header_t) + payload_length\nSince offset \u003e\u003d sizeof(ip6_header_t), this guarantees sr_len \u003c\u003d payload_length. The new guard sr_len \u003e payload_length can therefore never be true when sr0 is non-NULL. The underflow in payload_length - sr_len is already prevented by ip6_ext_header_walk() rejecting the packet before any of these functions are reached.\nMaybe replace the if (PREDICT_FALSE(...)) { error; return; } blocks with an ASSERT?\nThis is true for the other checks below too.",
      "revId": "24e1d24fe11d9351ddce2994bc142496250e61bd",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
