      "message": "We should assert on the expected error instead of log I think.\nTracing through the test case (plen\u003d30, 40-byte SRH in the buffer):\n - max_offset \u003d min(buffer_size, 40+30) \u003d 70\n - ip6_ext_header_len(srh) + 40 \u003d 40 + 40 \u003d 80 \u003e 70 → ip6_ext_header_walk() returns -1\n - sr0 \u003d NULL → packet dropped with SR_LOCALSID_ERROR_NO_SRH\n\nThe test checks for SRH_LEN_EXCEEDS_IP_LEN but I think the counter actually incremented is NO_SRH?",
